<BaseLayout
  title="Yoga Retreat on Sark Island | Sark Soul Island Retreats"
  description="Small-group yoga retreats on the car-free island of Sark. Daily yoga, vegetarian meals, wild swimming and stargazing on the world's first Dark Sky Island."
  path="/"
>
  <Hero
    eyebrow="Isle of Sark · Channel Islands"
    title="Yoga & Nature Retreats on Sark Island"
    line="Intimate five-night retreats on the world's first Dark Sky Island, half a day from London, a world away from everything else."
    shot="Clifftop coastal path at golden hour, Isle of Sark"
  />
  <AttributionStrip />

  <QRow
    question="What is the setting?"
    shot="The historic farmhouse and gardens, Sark"
    caption="A historic farmhouse by the sea, Sark"
  >
    <p>
      A small group, twice a year, in a historic farmhouse by the sea. Daily yoga, coastal walks,
      nourishing food, and the kind of quiet most people haven't experienced in years. The
      <a href="/retreats-on-sark">Late Summer Retreat</a> runs 12 to 17 September 2026, and 2027
      dates are coming soon.
    </p>
    <p>
      Sark Soul Island Retreats hosts intimate yoga retreats on Sark Island in the Channel Islands.
      Our small group immersions are designed for those seeking deep rest, reconnection and space
      away from mainland pace. This yoga retreat welcomes both experienced practitioners and
      curious newcomers.
    </p>
  </QRow>

  <DarkStrip
    eyebrow="The setting"
    title="The world's first Dark Sky Island"
  >
    <p>
      From the moment you step off the boat, distraction falls away. There are no cars, no
      streetlights, no rush. Daily yoga, coastal walks and nourishing seasonal food support genuine
      restoration, and when night falls, the world's first Dark Sky Island reveals its greatest
      gift. <a href="/why-sark">Discover why we chose Sark</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="hugo-quote">"There is no island in the world that I love more" · Victor Hugo</p>
  </DarkStrip>

  <QRow
    question="Who created these retreats?"
    flip
    shot="Nadia welcoming guests at the retreat house, Sark"
    caption="Created and hosted by Nadia"
  >
    <p>
      Sark Soul Island Retreats was founded by Nadia, who fell for the island's stillness and built
      a retreat around it. She hosts every gathering personally, and she's who you'll be speaking
      to from your first enquiry to your last morning.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/our-story">Read our story</a> or <a href="/meet-the-team">meet the team</a>.
    </p>
  </QRow>

  <QRow
    question="Who leads the practice?"
    shot="Monica teaching in the private yoga studio, Sark"
    caption="Yoga led by senior teacher Monica of YogaMorphic"
  >
    <p>
      Each day opens and closes with yoga. Morning practice to wake the body gently, evening
      practice to let the day settle. Monica Marini leads every session, drawing on around thirty
      years of teaching. Her style is warm and unhurried, with room for both seasoned practitioners
      and those returning to the mat after time away.
    </p>
    <p>
      You will never be pushed to perform. Sessions are small by design, so the teaching meets you
      where you are. Between practices, the days are yours: coastal walks, sea swims, quiet corners
      for rest. <a href="/the-practice">More about the practice</a>.
    </p>
  </QRow>

  <QRow
    question="What is a week here really like?"
    flip
    shot="Shared table in the farmhouse garden, Sark"
    caption="A place to arrive"
  >
    <p>
      Held within a historic farmhouse surrounded by stunning gardens, this is more than a
      beautiful setting, it is a place that naturally slows the body and quiets the mind. Spacious
      days, time to rest, sea air, coastal walks, turquoise coves, daily swims, shared meals, with
      morning and evening yoga framing the day.
    </p>
    <p>
      Sark sits a short <a href="https://sarkshipping.gg" rel="noopener">ferry from Guernsey</a>,
      around 55 minutes, half a day from London and a world away from everything else. Plenty of
      guests first meet the island on a day trip, then find themselves wanting more than a few
      hours. A week is how you really feel the place settle into you.
      <a href="/retreats-on-sark">Discover our retreats</a>.
    </p>
  </QRow>

  <Testimonials items={testimonials} />

  <PriceCards />

  <GuideSignup />

  <NadiaNote
    quote="I wanted somewhere the modern world could not follow us. Sark is that somewhere, and sharing it is the most transformative thing I do."
  />

  <CTABand
    title="Five nights on Sark this September"
    line="12 to 17 September 2026. Early booking rates end 19 July 2026."
  />
</BaseLayout>

